te the famous &quot;we are happy with the way this class is now&quot; etc.<br>
<br>
A few ideas that I brainstormed.  Fun but unlikely, I understand.<br>
<br>
1) Group buff that increases melee damage (a damage bonus to the weapon damage number based on %).  This could be a large bonus that wouldn't stack with haste or a smaller bonus that won't stack with the bard stacking haste.  Since this would increase melee damage output in a similar way that haste does stacking would be problem and could overpower melee.<br>
<br>
2) Decrease the damage number on the mob debuff.  Again it might not stack with slow if it was a significant downgrade to mob damage output.  Still a fun idea.<br>
<br>
3) Group mana preservation buff.  This would be the opposite of the mana regen buffs of enchanters so again maybe they wouldn't stack but give groups an alternative to having the enchanter.<br>
<br>
4) Mob debuff to increase mana usage per spell.<br>
<br>
Essentially these ideas are just another way to &quot;skin a cat&quot; where damage is changed instead of delay or mana preservation is used instead of mana regen.  Still it shows ways that Sony could make a wizard more group friendly if it wanted to.  Just one of these ideas would be useful (well maybe only 1-3) in getting wizards into groups more often.<br>
<br>
I know I am ignoring other classes like Mages but hey this is a wizard board after all.  Anyway if they gave wizards any of these spells the mages would scream about their focus effects being sucky. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101939"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Atri Drumrunner</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqdiva.com/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:darkblue;">Virtuoso</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:darkblue;">Erollisi Marr</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=191240"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Cameiel Stormgate</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.graffe.com/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:darkred;">Sorcerer</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.pendragons.org/everquest/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:darkred;">Pendragon Society</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enoah35>Enoah35</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 310<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/19/02 5:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizard desirability</span><hr size=1> I think the enhancement of the Atk for the group were already mentioned before. It goes more of a Mage or Enchanter role than us wizards. We wizards offer nothing more than damage, and if we do get the group buff then the melee version of wizard &gt; rogue would want another role, since they too offer damage only, considering most of their skill are irrelevant in grinding exp. <br>
<br>
We have been discussing what could bring us wizard without changing our nature of being damage dealers can become desirable to the group. Many ideas were brought and what I liked was the following.<br>
<br>
Make a mob highly resistant to melee damage (high AC) but vulnerable to Direct damages. Add some of these mobs as random pop in each zone. This won't change our nature of being magical damage dealers. Hence the holy trinity will suck big time since they are not doing enough damage to kill this mob for good exp group. Magicians, Necromancers and Wizards are the damage dealers in this situation. I believe this can bring up more desirability to not only us wizards but for other casters aswell. Since not only us wizards are terribly lacking of groups. Same can be said to other caster classes. The issue of the group taking mage and necro above us wizards because of their pets are irrelevant since the mob is highly resistant to melee. Appart from proc, the pet wont add much dsp eighther. <br>
<br>
Not the final solution. But its simply adding few of these mobs mixed with normal mobs are not a bad idea. It wont unbalance the game or class in anyway since they wont have to nerf any class nor improve what they got.<br>
<br>
Enoah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avgwiz>AvgWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/02 9:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard desirability</span><hr size=1> If they can add mobs that randomly see invis, invulnerable to snare/root, have high resists, and summon -- then they should add mobs that randomly high AC.  <br>
<br>
What do I mean by high AC?  Take the mobs current AC and add an additional 1000 AC to it.<br>
<br>
AvgWiz -- lvl 65 arcanist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tzeendao>Tzeen Dao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 299<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/02 1:08 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard desirability</span><hr size=1> I'd like to see a DD that adds +10% damage for every non-wizard in the group.<br>
<br>
I'd like to see wizards get information spells about the mobs current resistances.<br>
<br>
I'd like to see the anti-mob gate spell finally worked out.<br>
<br>
I'd like a Group Harvest spell. Without the stun.<br>
<br>
Those would be some nifty group orientated spells. I don't want buffs.<br>
<br>
pax,<br>
-Xoxxala <p><B><I><a href =http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9703>Xoxxala Oxxoxxulous</a> - Gnome Sorceror of E'ci</i> <Forlorn><BR><I>Tzeen Dao - Armadillo of E'ci</i></b><BR><I>Oft hope is born, when all are Forlorn</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=akaryn>Akaryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/02 4:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> spell suggestions</span><hr size=1> A few more spell suggestion:<br>
<br>
the ability to redirect magical energies- give wizzies a chance to rechannel energies cast by mobs. If successful we could turn the harmful spell back upon the mob, or give its self healing to our tank. This could  be a skill with a spell line that pops up the targets casting time window so we know when the spell is being cast and how long we havet to act. It should have a stun effect upon the wizard if successful and add to the wizards aggro list. <br>
<br>
Now, I am not going to debate the PoP and luclin ports for other players, to be honest we cant complain if it is necessary for them to enjoy the game, and it is. However, there are options to give us abilities to counter the apparent loss. <br>
<br>
Second bind point-<br>
Gives wizzies a second bind point with a second gate spell. this would give us travel advantages not available to any with PoP or luclin<br>
<br>
-Ports and tl's to our bind point- This spell would take the group or target to the wizzies bind point (primary or secondary if above spell is in effect). Now a wizard can be truly the class of travel, no more running thru dangerous zones multiple times to get groups or raids to an area,just get there, bind and everyone gets there easy with no chance of dying due to mobs. Oh, and no one gets lost. <br>
<br>
both of these adds to our groupability and minimizes our gains for soloing. <br>
<br>
More to come as I think of them.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=akaryn>Akaryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/20/02 5:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> More</span><hr size=1> Okay two more for now. <br>
Wizards are to be the masters of DD, well lets make them that.<br>
<br>
Give the wizard the ability to determine how much mana he wishes to put towards a spell. The more mana the more damage to probably as high as a good critical. Now this isnt like manaburn as the spell can be resisted and if it is you have lost that much more mana. This would be much more usefull in group and raids than soloing. And to be quite honest by the time we are soloing mobs that never resist our current spell they do not pose a threat. Ice giants never resist atols, or draught of fire, so why not be able to put lots of mana to one spell and get it killed quicker? Now for mobs that resist partially or completely, this skill would be a major mistake to use solo. <br>
<br>
Let us have a &quot;finishing&quot; skill where we dont have to have smaller spells memmed to finish a target off. We use our biggest nuke but it only does the minimum dam necessary to kill with an equivalently low mana usage. How many  times did the finishing spell cost more mana than the big nuke because you underestimated the targets remaining hit points and had to use it repeatedly?<br>
Mana conservation aids groups and raids alike for evac potential, but would not be a great gain in soloing. <br>
<br>
<br>
Feel free to tell me I am off my rocker or add suggestions <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mtyermom>MtYermom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/26/02 2:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More</span><hr size=1> I think the group harvest spell, in some form, is the most feasable.  The idea of a second bind point for wizzies is also interesting and something I've discussed with people before.  There arises, however, concern about exploits in giving us a second bind and/or the ability to port/TL people to our bind spots. <p>-Raelar Arcanus<br>
46th circle wizard of Solusek Ro<br>
Bertoxx server<br>
